.TH BACKFILL_CANONICAL 1 "2026-03-18" "stophammer" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
backfill_canonical \- rebuild canonical release and recording rows
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B backfill_canonical
[
.BI --db " PATH"
] [
.BI --limit " N"
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B backfill_canonical
rebuilds canonical release and recording rows, canonical promotions, and the
canonical search index for feeds already stored in the SQLite database. While
it runs, it coordinates with
.BR resolverd
via
.BR resolver_state.backfill_active .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --db " PATH"
Path to the SQLite database. Defaults to
.BR ./stophammer.db .
.TP
.BI --limit " N"
Limit the number of feeds processed, ordered by feed GUID.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Backfill the whole database:
.nf
cargo run --bin backfill_canonical -- --db ./stophammer.db
.fi
.TP
Backfill only the first 100 feeds:
.nf
cargo run --bin backfill_canonical -- --db ./stophammer.db --limit 100
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR stophammer (1),
.BR backfill_artist_identity (1),
.BR review_artist_identity (1)
